Testing if qemu-img creates images:
qemu-img create q.raw 12G
Formatting 'q.raw', fmt=raw size=12884901888
ok.
Testing for correct image size:
ls -l q.raw
-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 12884901888 Jul 18 20:40 q.raw
ok.
Testing if file is sparse:
ls -s q.raw
4 q.raw
ok.
Testing if conversion to a qcow2 image works:
qemu-img convert -f raw -O qcow2 q.raw q.qcow2
ok.
Checking if image is qcow2:
qemu-img info q.qcow2
image: q.qcow2
file format: qcow2
virtual size: 12 GiB (12884901888 bytes)
disk size: 196 KiB
cluster_size: 65536
Format specific information:
    compat: 1.1
    compression type: zlib
    lazy refcounts: false
    refcount bits: 16
    corrupt: false
    extended l2: false
